HEADWORD: Impendency
<hw>Im*pend"en*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of impending; the
state of being imminent and liable to happen soon; also, that which
impends.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Impendence</xex> of volcanic cloud.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Ruskin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> imminence, imminency, impendence,
forthcomingness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impendent</ent>⟦br⟧
